## Done-Gate (REAL commands, every one runs in this repo)

These exact commands must exit 0 to mark the feature complete. They run on the actual host, not aspirations.

```
[command 1, e.g. pytest tests/feature/ -v]
[command 2, e.g. python tools/verify_full_install.py]
[command 3, e.g. node tools/test_l3_intent.js]
```

## Power Pack Reality Contract (inherit)

- Every numeric claim ("<2s latency", "70% compression") is either measured upstream OR explicitly flagged as a hypothesis to verify in `/speckit-implement`.
- The Done-Gate is what `/ovo-audit` runs before allowing push.
- Micro-Commit Discipline: the sequencing section maps 1:1 onto the commit chain.
- Mistake #16: "code compiles" ≠ "feature works". Done-Gate is the only proof.
